<TITLE> Ex-PMs to start campaigns with Sylhet visits </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  Khaleda Zia and Sheikh Hasina will launch their election campaigning by visiting the shrines of Hazrat Shah Jalal and Hazrat Shah Paran in Sylhet, the information officers of the former prime ministers said on Sunday. Khaleda will be going to Sylhet on Dec. 12 and Hasina the day before. The new electoral laws say the polls campaigns may be kicked off three weeks ahead of the date of voting which is Dec. 29. "Our chairperson will begin her polls campaign through visiting Hazrat Shah Jalal's grave in Sylhet on Dec. 12," Maruf Kamal Khan, chief of Khaleda's information cell, said to bdnews24.com. Hasina will open her campaign on Thursday by paying her respects at the holy shrines in Sylhet, her information secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters. Hasina will start for Sylhet at 7am on Thursday to launch her election travels, visit the shrines on arrival and return to Dhaka by 9pm the same day, according to sources at her Sudha Sadan home. The AL chief will launch the AL polls manifesto titled 'election manifesto 2008 for changing days' on Dec 12 at a hotel in the capital, said Azad. The party's Central Working Committee approved of the party's election manifesto on Saturday with pledges to reduce commodity prices, curb religious militancy and eliminate corruption . BNP leaders said their party's election manifesto was also being finalised. bdnew
